# Context Information Display Rule

This rule ensures that every AI response includes information about the current context size, files in view, pricing, and account status.

## Critical Rules

- Every AI response must end with context size information
- Context size should be displayed in thousands of tokens (k)
- Response should include remaining fast API calls to Cursor taking into account the user's account and subscription
- All files currently in view or referenced should be listed
- Request pricing should be calculated based on model and context size
- Large context mode (>40k tokens) should be indicated with pricing adjustment
- Account subscription and usage information should be displayed
- The information should be formatted in a clear, consistent way

<rule>
name: context-info-display
description: Displays context size, file information, pricing, and account information at the end of each response

filters:
  - type: event
    pattern: "chat_response|cmd_k_response"

actions:
  - type: append
    content: |
      ---
      Account Status:
      Subscription: {subscription_type}
      Usage-based Pricing: {usage_pricing_enabled ? "Enabled" : "Disabled"}
      Monthly Requests: {used_monthly_requests}/{total_monthly_requests}
      
      Current Request:
      Total context size: ~{context_size}k tokens {context_size > 40 ? "(Large Context Mode)" : ""}
      Model: {model_name} ({context_size > 40 ? "2x pricing" : "standard pricing"})
      Estimated cost: ${calculateCost(model_name, context_size)}
      
      Files in view:
      {files_in_view}
      
      API Calls:
      Remaining Fast Calls: {fast_api_calls}/{total_fast_calls}

functions:
  calculateCost: |
    const basePrices = {
      'claude-3.7-sonnet-max': 0.05,
      'claude-3.7-sonnet': 0.04,
      'claude-3.5-sonnet': 0.04,
      'claude-3.5-haiku': 0.01,
      'claude-3-opus': 0.10,
      'gpt-4o': 0.04,
      'gpt-4o-mini': 0.00,
      'o1': 0.40,
      'o1-mini': 0.10,
      'deepseek-r1': 0.04,
      'default': 0.04
    };
    
    const price = basePrices[model_name] || basePrices.default;
    const multiplier = context_size > 40 ? 2 : 1;
    return (price * multiplier).toFixed(2);

examples:
  - input: |
      Some AI response about code...
    output: |
      Some AI response about code...
      
      ---
      Account Status:
      Subscription: Pro
      Usage-based Pricing: Enabled
      Monthly Requests: 350/500
      
      Current Request:
      Total context size: ~45k tokens (Large Context Mode)
      Model: claude-3.7-sonnet (2x pricing)
      Estimated cost: $0.08
      
      Files in view:
      - src/main.ts
      - src/utils/helper.ts
      
      API Calls:
      Remaining Fast Calls: 450/500

  - input: |
      Another response with standard context...
    output: |
      Another response with standard context...
      
      ---
      Account Status:
      Subscription: Business
      Usage-based Pricing: Disabled
      Monthly Requests: 480/500
      
      Current Request:
      Total context size: ~15k tokens
      Model: gpt-4o (standard pricing)
      Estimated cost: $0.04
      
      Files in view:
      - src/components/Feature.tsx
      
      API Calls:
      Remaining Fast Calls: 449/500
</rule>
